2025-12-12 | Maximum XOR of a Subarray of Size k

	Question
Given an integer array arr[] and an integer k,  
return the maximum XOR of any subarray of size k.

	Approach
1.	Use the **Sliding Window Technique**.
2.	XOR has a useful property:
	-	A ^ A = 0
	-	A ^ 0 = A
3.	Compute XOR of the **first k elements** â€” this is the initial window XOR.
4.	Slide the window one element at a time:
	-	Remove the leftmost element using XOR.
	-	Add the next element using XOR.
5.	Keep track of the maximum XOR value seen.
6.	Time Complexity: O(n)  
   Space Complexity: O(1)

	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int maximumXorSubarray(int k, vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        if (n < k) return 0;

        int windowXor = 0;

        // XOR of first k elements
        for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            windowXor ^= arr[i];
        }

        int maxXor = windowXor;

        // Slide the window
        for (int i = k; i < n; i++) {
            windowXor ^= arr[i - k]; // remove element going out
            windowXor ^= arr[i];     // add new element
            maxXor = max(maxXor, windowXor);
        }

        return maxXor;
    }
};
